“Can we continue to service external debts with 90% of our revenue? It is a path to destruction. It is not sustainable. We must make the very difficult changes that are necessary for our country to get up from slumber.”

President Bola Tinubu has ruled out sustaining the economic policy of the immediate past President Muhammadu Buhari.

"Me sef I be Jagun Jagun of Afro-fusion."

Video of Burna Boy hailing Nollywood movie Jagun Jagun by Femi Adebayo goes viral. He was seen hanging out with Asake in the clip. 

Someone reacted to the video: "Dem no go see this one talk o, Burna promoting Jagun Jagun."

Following the news that the Lagdo Dam in Cameroon will soon release water, would-be affected states have urged residents of flood-prone areas to relocate to higher lands.

The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA) had earlier issued an alert over a looming flood on the banks of River Benue.

The presidency says any minister who does not meet expectations will be sacked.

Presidential spokesman Ajuri Ngelale on Monday, August 28, said President Bola Tinubu will not tolerate failure from his recently inaugurated ministers.

“He is not somebody that is afraid to levy quick sanctions to ensure that they get the results that he wants,” Ngelale said.

Kids who were taken on an ice cream date by their aunty decided to start asking questions.

They asked why she was living alone without a man or at least a dog in her life.

"Being single is now a crime," someone reacted to the video.

Nigerian socialite Pretty Mike sparks emotions after leaving a comment on the best and worst BBL by a Nigerian celebrity.

The Night life boss revealed on a podcast that the best is that of former reality star, Kokobykhloe and the worst is that of relationship expert, Blessing Ceo.

"He who finds a wife finds a good thing!"🥰

An adorable video of recently evicted BBNaija's Frodd's wife speaking to him as she beamed with excitement has left many gushing.

"A win is a win. He left the show to go home to the real price," a fan said.

Imo gospel singer, Amaka Gift, who was called out by her estranged lover for dumping him, has finally shed light on the matter. 

The singer accused Favour of being a woman beater and countered his marriage claims. 

She said she was done with the matter. Amaka shared her side of the story briefly with Legit.ng.

Another wahala!

Just like Godwin Emefiele, the new acting CBN governor is set to face a legal battle to clear his name.

A group has decided to sue him in court, and the case has been admitted.

The coup leader in Niger Republic has taken another hard measure against France by cutting off water and electricity supply to the Embassy and consulates in the country.

This development is coming days after the French Ambassador, Sylvain Itte was ordered to leave Niger Republic within 48 hours.

"Omoluabi."

A viral clip of Nigerian singer Davido greeting his uncle's friends and Ooni of Ife's wife by prostrating trends.  

One netizen reacted to the trending clip: "See simplicity  Yoruba Culture, heritage and respect."

"Vee dey craze. She was actually having fun watching TBaj disgrace herself."

It's been a chaotic online moment following Tolani Bj's eviction, as BBNaija Vee, Tacha, and Eric shade the contentious disc jockey.

"I feel Neo and TBaj have a situation outside that house. It isn't possible that Tolani can just be acting like a puppet queen," another fan wrote.

From riding bicycle to owning a car, a Nigerian man has been blessed after meeting Pastor Chibuzor of OPM!

Apostle Chibuzor Chinere, has rewarded a pastor who rode a bicycle from Benue state to see him in Rivers with a car and N100,000.

He also offered one of the man's children an automatic overseas university scholarship.

It's lonely at the top, ghen ghen ghen ghen ghen ghen!🤯

Iyabo Ojo, who is currently in Canada, has shared a sweet video of her showing different moves after one of her goddaughters blessed her with $1000 (N774K), which caused a buzz online.

Quoted companies in trouble!

NGX asked 26 companies to pay N125 million fine for not submitting their financial report on time

The companies include banking and non-banking service providers such as Unity Bank, FBN Holdings, Access Holdings, John Holt, PZ Cussons and others.
money on my mind

Former Kaduna lawmaker, Shehu Sani has thrown shade at the minister of works, David Umahi.

Sani said, “Brother Umahi is holding the Senate seat with his right hand and the ministerial seat with the left hand; just in case of the change of weather.”

Reacting, someone wrote, “Man no wan loose guard.”

A Nigerian man told his wife to collect a package from a friend that was coming to the UK.

Unknown to the wife, it was her husband coming with a surprise.

Her reaction when she saw him was captured in the video.

A throwback video from Steve Harvey's game show Family Feud, where his wife Marjorie suggested she would cheat on him with a "pool boy," has gone viral and left many talking.

"I was always scared for Uncle Steve. She looked too good for his age," a netizen said.

"You people should report him to Odumeje. Or Pastor Eze," a man suggested. 

A Nigerian man has taken his sister and her husband's names and pictures to a shrine as he summoned them before it. 

In a video, the herbalist of the shrine showed the couple's details as he warned them of the consequences should they fail to heed his directive.
